# 5. 撮影開始！

Nene: Oh, um... Amisawa, do you have a minute? I want to ask you a few things about the film equipment...
Nene: Hm? What are you watching...?
Amisawa: Huh? Oh, this? It's drone footage. The person took shots from a bunch of different angles instead of just from up above.
Nene: Yeah, and they took some really nice footage.
Amisawa: Isn't it amazing how much technology has advanced? Did you know that people started making motion pictures all the way back in the 19th century? It began with this device called a “cinematograph”.
Amisawa: Oh, sorry! I didn't mean to get sidetracked! Asking my dad about this stuff sorta lit this fire inside of me...
Nene: No, that's okay... I can tell that you like cameras very much.
Nene: I'm also really interested in that, but... Mind if I ask about the equipment...?
Soda: Hiyaaah!
Nene: Soda, what are you doing...?
Soda: Oh, I was just practicing for the film! I've been going to this one judo dojo for a really long time, and the kids there said they wanted to see our film.
Nene: I see... That explains why you sound so motivated.
Soda: Yeah, I'm going to do whatever it takes! Get ready for some really cool fight scenes!
Nene: *Nod* I'll be looking forward to those...
Nene: T-Tachibana...? You've been staring at me for a while now. Is there something on my face...?
Tachibana: Hmm... No, it's not that. Hey, Director, wanna go clothes shopping together sometime?
Nene: What?! Why...?
Tachibana: After watching you work, I kinda want to dress you up in some nice clothes, you know...?
Nene: U-Uhh, lemme think about it...
An: Hey, Kusanagi. What can I do to become a better actor?
Nene: Huh? Wh-Why do you ask?
An: I tried recording a video of myself acting, but my delivery was a bit...no, really stiff...
An: I wanna go all out, especially for the last part! Can you teach me how to sound more convincing?!
Akito: Yeah, I wanna learn how to do that too. The cast needs to be on top of their game for this film.
Nene: O-Okay. I might not be the best teacher, but...
An: Don't say that! Please teach us, Kusanagi!
Nene: A-Alright, so...
Nene: (We finally start shooting tomorrow...)
Nene: (We've been really busy until today, but I've had a chance to talk to everyone... I feel a lot more comfortable around them now...)
Nene: (I hope our shoot goes well...)
An: Wow... This is where we're shooting?
Female Students: This is awesome...! Just look at those cliffs! It's the perfect location!
Nene: Amisawa's group found it for us. It really is an amazing location.
An: We finally get to start shooting! This is so exciting! You memorized all of your lines, right, Akito?
Akito: Of course. I'm not about to make a fool of myself.
An: You sure are pumped up. But that checks out!
An: Still, to think that you'd be chosen for the lead.
Akito: I mean, we didn't really have a choice... I'm the only one who's more or less the same height and build as Soda.
Soda: Sorry, Shinonome... If only my acting skills were a little better...
Soda: My brain and body sorta need to be doing the same thing, you know? My muscles do all the talking for me!
An: Yeah, I get that. Also, no one's good at everything.
Akito: True... But the fight scenes are gonna be your time to shine. Do your best as my stunt double.
Nene: You're also playing an important role, Shiraishi... The girl who the hero saves... You have a lot on your plate, but I hope you'll give it your best.
An: Will do!
Tachibana: Alright, actors, once you've finished changing, please hurry on over here so I can start doing your makeup!
An: Oh, gotta go...! See you in a bit, Kusanagi!
Nene: (We're really gonna start shooting soon...)
Nene: (I've had to learn a lot of new things for this, but I need to do my best as the director...!)
Amisawa: The lights and camera are all set, Director!
Nene: O-Okay, thanks.
Nene: (Now, the cast should be...)
An: We're good to go whenever!
Nene: (All ready to go...)
Nene: (We're starting with the scene where the girl gets attacked by the Dark Cooks and the hero comes to save her...)
Nene: (It's also the opening scene, making it a really important one... Ideally, we'll get this right and set the stage for the rest of our shoot.)
Nene: Okay, everyone... And...
Nene: Action!
Girl: “Huff... Huff... I'm almost home...”
Girl: “But I'm so hungry...”
Girl: “Maybe if I had just a little... No, stop! Mom's sick! She needs this more than me!”
Girl: “I'm almost there, Mom. You'll get to have some food in a little bit...!”
Nene: (Shiraishi's doing a really good job... She's still a little stiff here and there, but she isn't hesitating. That makes her sound really natural...)
Dark Cook A: “Hah hah hah! Where do you think you're going, little girl?!”
Dark Cook B: “Oh, what's this?! Your bag is full of... Food!”
Dark Cook C: “What a stroke of luck! I guess this is what they mean by a duck carrying a leek!”
Girl: “N-No...! You're...”
Dark Cook A: “Bad luck, darling. This food now belongs to the... U-Uhh... The Dark Culinary Society!”
Nene: Cut!
Male Student A: S-Sorry, I forgot my line.
Male Student B: Yeah, and my voice sounded really shrill there for a second...
Nene: N-No, that's okay... This was our first take after all.
Nene: (Still, what should I say to them...? I don't think telling them to sound natural will help...)
Nene: Um, so... Are you guys feeling nervous because we're actually shooting now?
Male Student A: Yeah... We practiced a ton, but this is for real now...
Male Student A: The thought of everyone at school seeing our film keeps overwhelming my brain...
Nene: Right...
Nene: (Wait, what if...?)
Nene: Then, why don't we take some deep breaths and relax... After that...
Nene: Let's try thinking about having more fun...
An: Fun?
Nene: Yeah. A lot of you are acting for the first time, so I'm sure you're worried about how you're gonna do and stuff...
Nene: But I believe the most important thing is to enjoy playing your characters...
Male Student A: We should enjoy playing our characters...?
Nene: Yeah... I know how you all feel since I lost sight of that once a long time ago, which didn't end well for me.
Male Student A: Kusanagi...
Male Student B: Yeah... I think I know what she's talking about. But for now... We should all try to have more fun!
Male Student B: Okay! Then, next take?
Nene: Yeah...!
Amisawa: Break time! Don't forget to stay hydrated, everyone!
Nene: Phew...
Nene: (Our shoot's going pretty well.)
Nene: (I wasn't sure how things were gonna go at first, but it's been smooth. I really can't thank everyone enough for...)
Tachibana: Surprise!
Nene: Eep...! S-So cold...!
Amisawa: Haha. We brought you some ice-cold juice. We had it chill specially for our dear director.
Nene: Huh? This is for me...?
Tachibana: Yeah, because you've been working the hardest out of all of us!
Nene: I don't think that's true... But thanks. I'll gladly have this.
Amisawa: Great! Also... This drink is a small token of our appreciation.
Nene: It is...?
Amisawa: Yeah, because...
Amisawa: We know our film's gonna be amazing now!
Amisawa: We put you in a tough spot when we asked you to become the director, but it's coming along really nicely now, don't you think?
Tachibana: Yeah, it totally is. Without her, this thing was probably doomed to become one of those really bad home videos or something.
Amisawa: Exactly. But you've been doing such an awesome job as the director... Our film's starting to look good, which is giving us even more motivation!
Nene: I-I've been doing a good job...?
Amisawa: Yeah, so...! Let's see this through until the end and make our film an amazing one!
Nene: ...
Nene: Yeah...
Nene: Let's keep doing our best. Together.
